text: A prototype fence model has been added to the game. There are three defined states: north-south, east-west and a cross. These models are currently unused.
Nothing can be placed on top of fences.
Fences do not connect to solid blocks.
The player no longer starts with fences in their inventory.[needs testing]
Standing on top of fences causing players to get stuck and crashing the server in multiplayer have now been fixed.
Fences are now flammable and the visibility of them has now been improved.[more information needed]
The application of textures to the fence model has been changed slightly.
Any block,[verify] including torches and other fences, are now able to be placed on fences.
Added villages and strongholds, where wooden fences naturally generate.
Dropped fence items no longer appear larger than normal blocks.
Fences no longer require a solid block underneath to be placed.
Added Nether fortresses, including Nether brick fences.
The collision boxes of fences have now been reduced.
Fences now connect to solid blocks.
Fence selection area has now been changed to match its collision box.
The texture of planks was slightly changed, resulting in fences also changing appearance.
Fences no longer prevent farmland from decaying when placed below farmland.
It is now possible to place pressure plates on top of Nether brick fences.
Mobs no longer try to jump over Nether brick fences.[more information needed]
The texture of fences has now been fixed. There was a problem when attached single slab or stairs because the face not rendered when attached other blocks.[1]
Fence corners now have a smaller collision box, allowing players to fall through the gap in the middle of four fences placed in a square.
Mobs can now be tied to fences.
Fences now display a useless hand animation when right clicked.
The nether brick fence item model is now a flat plane.
Nether brick fences now have a proper item model again.[2]

Fences now have a new crafting recipe using 4 planks of the same type to produce 3 fences. Previously, it required six sticks in a 2×3 grid to produce 2.
[show]
Old Recipe
Fences now vary in appearance based on the planks used to make them.
"Fence" has now been renamed to "Oak Fence".
Fences now show glitchy elongated textures when connecting to other fences.[3] These may be GPU dependent.
Fences now no longer show a bugged texture, however they appear different to how they did prior to 15w44b.
The correct fence wood types now generate in villages.
Oak, birch and dark oak wood fences now generate in woodland mansions.
Fences now no longer show a useless hand animation when right clicked.
Fences now connect to the solid back sides of stairs.
The oak fence ID has now been changed from fence to oak_fence.
It is now possible to place a fence when the player is within a corner of three fences to form a ring of four, provided the space is sufficient.
Prior to The Flattening, these blocks' numeral IDs were 85, 113, 188, 189, 190, 191 and 192.
Water can now be placed on the same block as fences.
The textures of fences have now been changed.

Nether brick fence recipe has now been changed to avoid conflict with the Nether brick wall recipe.
[show]
Old Recipe
The textures of fences have now been changed.
Spruce fences now generate in the newly added snowy tundra villages.
The updated desert villages now generate with jungle fences instead of oak fences.
The texture of spruce fences has now been changed.
Wood fences can now be used to craft composters.
Fences are no longer used to craft composters.
Crimson and warped fences now connect to other types of fences.[4]
Survival players no longer start out with an infinite amount of fences in the inventory.
Fences now naturally spawn in strongholds, mineshafts and villages.
Added spruce, birch, jungle, acacia and dark oak variants.
"Fence" has now been renamed to "Oak Fence".
Torches can now be placed on top of Nether brick fences.
Spruce wood fences now generate in witch huts.
The texture of Nether brick fences is now brighter.
Savanna villages now generate with acacia wood fences rather than oak fences.
Spruce wood fences now generate in taiga, snowy tundra and snowy taiga villages.
Oak, birch and dark oak wood fences now generate in woodland mansions.
Wooden fences now generate in shipwrecks.
The recipe for Nether brick fences has now been changed to avoid conflict with the Nether brick wall recipe.
The textures of fences have now been changed.
Dark oak fence gates now generate in pillager outposts.
Due to architecture changes, oak fences no longer generate in desert villages.
Jungle fences now generate in desert village armorers.
The texture of Nether brick fences now matches Java Edition's again.
Crimson and warped fences now uses regular plank sounds instead of their stem variant sounds.
Pressure plates are now placeable on fences.
The fence collision box has now been decreased to size of fence block.
Added spruce, birch, and jungle variants.
The crafting recipe now uses 4 planks and 2 sticks instead of 6 sticks.
"Fence" has now been renamed to "Oak Fence".
Added acacia and dark oak fences to the creative inventory. When they were actually added to the game is unknown.
Fences now connect to the solid back sides of stairs.
The textures of fences have now been changed.
